// task_a.su — the Linux 0.00 "task A" analogue.
//
// Linux 0.00's task A is a hardcoded loop that writes 'A' forever;
// the timer interrupt switches to task B. The Yantra-native
// realization (see planning/21-linux-0.00.md): a trivial Sutra
// service the Connectome Manager ticks. Each tick (the timer-IRQ
// analogue) it emits the ASCII codepoint of 'A' — 65 — as a real
// substrate number-vector via `real_number`. This is NOT a faked
// 'A': the emitted vector genuinely carries the value chr(65)=='A'
// on the real axis, decodable host-side by the monitoring
// `.real()` accessor (CLAUDE.md: accessors are monitoring-only and
// allowed). `make_real` is a substrate op — no host shortcut.
//
// The inbound axon is the tick trigger and is deliberately ignored,
// exactly as Linux 0.00's task ignores everything and just writes
// its letter.

function vector on_axon(vector input_axon) {
    return real_number(65.0);
}
